⁰ Mayhoff supposes that there is a lacuna before drachmam : ‘⁴ excidit dari vel aliud quid, unde pendeat drachmam.” Possibly drachmam is governed by dedere above. Both eadem . . . facerent and buylosso . . . liberari—especially the latter—look like later additions. Pliny, who was fond of parentheses, may have added one or both of them as an after- thought, overlooking the fact that so doing upset the syntax of the passage.
